00:34:25,890 --> 00:34:26,840
- What do you want?

538
00:34:28,773 --> 00:34:29,606
- No.

539
00:34:36,357 --> 00:34:37,190
But, Mom?

540
00:34:39,714 --> 00:34:41,297
Could you be close?

541
00:34:42,620 --> 00:34:44,028
- Mmm-hmm.

542
00:34:44,028 --> 00:34:46,445
(soft music)

543
00:34:56,647 --> 00:34:59,397
(birds chirping)

544
00:35:01,567 --> 00:35:04,180
- Honey, she's just late.

545
00:35:04,180 --> 00:35:05,377
- She's not coming.

546
00:35:08,880 --> 00:35:09,713
- Andrea.

547
00:35:12,543 --> 00:35:13,626
- Wait, wait.

548
00:35:17,760 --> 00:35:20,012
I was early, and I thought.

549
00:35:20,012 --> 00:35:22,762
(hard breathing)

550
00:35:26,323 --> 00:35:27,156
Doughnut?

551
00:35:30,107 --> 00:35:30,940
Brad?

552
00:35:43,083 --> 00:35:44,783
What time should I bring her home?

553
00:35:46,960 --> 00:35:48,110
- We'll just wait here.

554
00:35:50,429 --> 00:35:51,346
- Oh, okay.

555
00:35:57,853 --> 00:35:58,686
So.

556
00:36:09,685 --> 00:36:12,602
(soft piano music)

557
00:36:46,330 --> 00:36:49,170
- Brad, that tree doesn't
look very strong, honey.

558
00:36:49,170 --> 00:36:50,003
Be careful.

559
00:36:56,002 --> 00:36:58,585
(dogs barking)

560
00:37:11,180 --> 00:37:13,840
- [Cathy] It's a long time
since I been in this park.

561
00:37:13,840 --> 00:37:15,380
- [Andrea] Why, where do you live?

562
00:37:15,380 --> 00:37:16,700
- [Cathy] I live in Chicago.

563
00:37:16,700 --> 00:37:19,263
- [Andrea] Oh, is it really that windy.

564
00:37:21,090 --> 00:37:21,993
- Oh yeah, yeah.

565
00:37:35,950 --> 00:37:37,530
What?

566
00:37:37,530 --> 00:37:40,220
- Nothing, you, you just don't look like

567
00:37:40,220 --> 00:37:41,323
your old pictures.

568
00:37:44,120 --> 00:37:46,360
- You have pictures of me?

569
00:37:46,360 --> 00:37:49,123
- Yeah, up in the attic, just a couple.

570
00:37:52,080 --> 00:37:53,230
- Can I see your thumb?

571
00:38:00,970 --> 00:38:04,780
You used to suck it so hard
you'd get these big blisters.

572
00:38:04,780 --> 00:38:07,143
I was afraid they'd scar up and stay.

573
00:38:09,573 --> 00:38:13,420
- No.

574
00:38:13,420 --> 00:38:14,253
- No.

575
00:38:19,230 --> 00:38:21,313
- We have the same hands.

576
00:38:23,740 --> 00:38:24,803
- Long fingers.

577
00:38:34,820 --> 00:38:38,333
- I'm really, really sorry
about the orange juice.

578
00:38:39,289 --> 00:38:42,206
(soft piano music)

579
00:38:47,832 --> 00:38:49,915
(crying)

580
00:39:14,085 --> 00:39:16,668
(kids yelling)

581
00:39:32,407 --> 00:39:34,490
- Ahhh, Mom, Mom, please!

582
00:39:35,593 --> 00:39:39,140
Mom, Mom, Mom, please, get my mom.

583
00:39:39,140 --> 00:39:41,490
- Brad, honey, I'm here.

584
00:39:41,490 --> 00:39:43,350
Excuse me, honey, don't move, don't move.

585
00:39:43,350 --> 00:39:44,880
Okay, where does it hurt?

586
00:39:44,880 --> 00:39:45,713
- My ankle.

587
00:39:45,713 --> 00:39:46,960
- Okay, which ankle?
- Left.

588
00:39:46,960 --> 00:39:48,390
- Okay, don't move.

589
00:39:48,390 --> 00:39:49,800
How in God's name did you do this?

590
00:39:49,800 --> 00:39:50,760
We need to get you to the hospital.

591
00:39:50,760 --> 00:39:52,280
- Do you want me to call an ambulance?

592
00:39:52,280 --> 00:39:53,750
- Yes, please.

593
00:39:53,750 --> 00:39:56,020
Wait a minute, where's Andrea?

594
00:39:56,020 --> 00:39:57,780
Can you stay with him for a minute?

595
00:39:57,780 --> 00:39:58,613
- Sure, sure.

596
00:39:58,613 --> 00:39:59,446
- Don't move, honey.

597
00:40:00,320 --> 00:40:01,859
- Man, how did you do this anyway?

598
00:40:01,859 --> 00:40:02,692
- Andrea.

599
00:40:03,949 --> 00:40:04,782
Andrea.

600
00:40:09,640 --> 00:40:11,120
We can't wait.

601
00:40:11,120 --> 00:40:12,400
Honey, don't put any weight on it.

602
00:40:12,400 --> 00:40:13,290
- [Man] Let me get it.

603
00:40:13,290 --> 00:40:14,980
- Great, thank you.

604
00:40:14,980 --> 00:40:17,260
It's okay, it's okay.

605
00:40:17,260 --> 00:40:19,177
- I got you, I got you.

606
00:40:21,730 --> 00:40:23,065
- What happened?

607
00:40:23,065 --> 00:40:24,850
- I think Brad broke his leg.

608
00:40:24,850 --> 00:40:26,080
We're going to the hospital.

609
00:40:26,080 --> 00:40:26,970
- We'll follow you.

610
00:40:26,970 --> 00:40:28,310
- No.

611
00:40:28,310 --> 00:40:29,850
- Come on, Andrea.

612
00:40:29,850 --> 00:40:30,683
- Mom.

613
00:40:32,928 --> 00:40:34,028
Do you really need me?

614
00:40:35,793 --> 00:40:37,510
- Why don't I take Andrea home?

615
00:40:37,510 --> 00:40:39,410
That way, you can concentrate on Brad.

616
00:40:42,240 --> 00:40:43,193
- Go straight home.

617
00:40:48,220 --> 00:40:50,020
- Now your left ear.

618
00:40:50,020 --> 00:40:51,440
No, this is nothing.

619
00:40:51,440 --> 00:40:53,290
People come in here all the time,

620
00:40:53,290 --> 00:40:54,600
bones speared through the skin,

621
00:40:54,600 --> 00:40:56,040
limbs hanging by tendons.

622
00:40:56,040 --> 00:40:56,873
- Gross.

623
00:40:56,873 --> 00:40:58,003
- Let me look in your eye.

624
00:40:59,449 --> 00:41:02,460
- Ah, a casualty.

625
00:41:02,460 --> 00:41:03,960
- Hi, Joe.

626
00:41:03,960 --> 00:41:05,550
- So what happened to you?

627
00:41:05,550 --> 00:41:06,833
- I jumped off a statue.

628
00:41:08,300 --> 00:41:09,930
- Sure, why not?

629
00:41:09,930 --> 00:41:11,660
- Hairline fracture in the tibia.

630
00:41:11,660 --> 00:41:13,510
Some pulled ligaments, no hemorrhage.

631
00:41:16,220 --> 00:41:17,053
- Yep.

632
00:41:19,130 --> 00:41:21,980
So, you want plaster or one of those

633
00:41:21,980 --> 00:41:23,810
fancy athletic braces?

634
00:41:23,810 --> 00:41:25,280
- Athletic brace.

635
00:41:25,280 --> 00:41:26,433
- You got it, cowboy.

636
00:41:27,340 --> 00:41:30,350
- [P.A.] Dr. Cottrell, Dr. Janet Cottrell.

637
00:41:30,350 --> 00:41:31,563
Emergency admitting.

638
00:41:33,190 --> 00:41:34,540
- How did you meet Anthony?

639
00:41:35,870 --> 00:41:38,023
- He hired me for the counter.

640
00:41:39,370 --> 00:41:41,710
It paid well, and I always liked jewelry.

641
00:41:41,710 --> 00:41:44,750
It's not like one of those
junky little mall chains.

642
00:41:44,750 --> 00:41:46,453
It's a nice old family business.

643
00:41:47,320 --> 00:41:49,160
His dad was a pearl man.

644
00:41:49,160 --> 00:41:50,463
- So you're a salesgirl?

645
00:41:52,260 --> 00:41:53,210
- Started that way.

646
00:41:55,210 --> 00:41:57,760
But then I got into the
gems and wanted to move up.

647
00:41:58,800 --> 00:42:00,200
Anthony was very supportive.

648
00:42:01,760 --> 00:42:04,360
Even paid for me to go to
the Gemological Institute.

649
00:42:06,010 --> 00:42:07,460
So now I have my certificate.

650
00:42:13,300 --> 00:42:14,133
- What's this?

651
00:42:18,110 --> 00:42:20,633
- Amethyst, Brazilian.

652
00:42:22,270 --> 00:42:23,103
Pretty.

653
00:42:24,330 --> 00:42:25,403
Semi-precious.

654
00:42:27,700 --> 00:42:28,800
- Tandy gave it to me.

655
00:42:39,477 --> 00:42:42,644
- Did your dad ever tell you about me?

656
00:42:44,420 --> 00:42:45,270
Did you ever ask?

657
00:42:46,140 --> 00:42:47,173
- Not after a while.

658
00:42:50,860 --> 00:42:52,680
- I left home when I was 13.

659
00:42:55,262 --> 00:42:57,594
(phone ringing)

660
00:42:57,594 --> 00:43:01,720
- [P.A.] IV nurse, call the
fourth-floor nurses station.

661
00:43:01,720 --> 00:43:02,870
- I shoulda kept an eye on him.

662
00:43:02,870 --> 00:43:05,630
He was antsy, and when he
gets antsy he gets so--

663
00:43:05,630 --> 00:43:07,630
- Laura, he's fine.

664
00:43:07,630 --> 00:43:09,273
- No, he's not.

665
00:43:12,460 --> 00:43:13,933
Their mother's back.

666
00:43:15,190 --> 00:43:16,023
- What?

667
00:43:16,023 --> 00:43:17,570
- Cathy, their mother,

668
00:43:17,570 --> 00:43:20,013
she's in town.

669
00:43:25,987 --> 00:43:29,280
(phone ringing)

670
00:43:29,280 --> 00:43:30,330
- Have they seen her?

671
00:43:31,970 --> 00:43:33,203
- Andrea's with her now.

672
00:43:36,290 --> 00:43:38,210
What will this do to them?

673
00:43:38,210 --> 00:43:39,280
- What do you mean?

674
00:43:39,280 --> 00:43:40,113
- Emotionally.

675
00:43:41,520 --> 00:43:42,710
Look, I know you're not a shrink,

676
00:43:42,710 --> 00:43:44,210
but you are their doctor,
and you've known them

677
00:43:44,210 --> 00:43:46,630
almost as long as I have,
and everything they've

678
00:43:46,630 --> 00:43:48,440
been through, and this
can't be good for them.

679
00:43:48,440 --> 00:43:50,170
This could do permanent damage, right?

680
00:43:50,170 --> 00:43:51,990
- Look, Laura, I think we're all

681
00:43:51,990 --> 00:43:54,193
permanently damaged by our parents.

682
00:43:57,947 --> 00:44:02,230
- [P.A] Dr. Cohen to radiology,
Dr. Cohen to radiology.

683
00:44:02,230 --> 00:44:04,580
- You are a terrific
mom, and they love you.

684
00:44:04,580 --> 00:44:09,340
But this is somebody too.

685
00:44:09,340 --> 00:44:10,900
- Brad says she's not his mother.

686
00:44:10,900 --> 00:44:12,441
- [Joe] Okay, so he's not
ready to deal with it yet.

687
00:44:12,441 --> 00:44:13,900
- And Andrea's at such
an impressionable age.

688
00:44:13,900 --> 00:44:14,850
- She's a bright girl.

689
00:44:14,850 --> 00:44:15,700
- She's just a child.

690
00:44:15,700 --> 00:44:16,788
- What are you afraid of?

691
00:44:16,788 --> 00:44:18,800
- What do you think I'm afraid of?

692
00:44:18,800 --> 00:44:21,401
This woman is going to
take away my children.

693
00:44:21,401 --> 00:44:24,690
- Laura, come on.

694
00:44:24,690 --> 00:44:26,250
What is she to them?

695
00:44:26,250 --> 00:44:29,870
A ghost, a mystery, a question
that needs to be answered.

696
00:44:29,870 --> 00:44:30,983
But not a mother.

697
00:44:32,070 --> 00:44:32,903
That's you.

698
00:44:35,777 --> 00:44:36,627
And they know it.

699
00:44:40,030 --> 00:44:41,180
- How'd you meet Daddy?

700
00:44:44,095 --> 00:44:44,928
- At a car wash.

701
00:44:46,576 --> 00:44:48,583
He brought his church group or something.

702
00:44:50,770 --> 00:44:52,453
He drove up in this red Camaro.

703
00:44:55,150 --> 00:44:56,723
He was older, cute.

704
00:44:58,336 --> 00:44:59,486
- And you got pregnant?

705
00:45:03,220 --> 00:45:04,527
- Not right away, but--

706
00:45:04,527 --> 00:45:06,668
- And you got married.

707
00:45:06,668 --> 00:45:07,501
And you had me.

708
00:45:10,430 --> 00:45:12,680
- Yes, I did.

709
00:45:12,680 --> 00:45:14,833
- Then you had Brad, and then you left.

710
00:45:18,999 --> 00:45:19,832
- Yeah.

711
00:45:22,092 --> 00:45:22,925
I did.

712
00:45:24,063 --> 00:45:25,703
- Because you didn't love us.

713
00:45:27,100 --> 00:45:28,150
- No.

714
00:45:28,150 --> 00:45:30,660
- Then why, did Daddy do something?

715
00:45:30,660 --> 00:45:31,493
- No, no.

716
00:45:34,208 --> 00:45:35,208
It wasn't his fault.

717
00:45:36,733 --> 00:45:37,983
He did the best he could.

718
00:45:39,440 --> 00:45:41,640
I wasn't much older
than you when I had you.

719
00:45:44,290 --> 00:45:45,950
I was too immature.

720
00:45:45,950 --> 00:45:49,133
I, I couldn't.

721
00:45:52,089 --> 00:45:54,589
(dog barking)

722
00:45:55,793 --> 00:45:57,553
I never wanted to hurt you, Andrea.

723
00:46:00,790 --> 00:46:01,843
That's why I left.

724
00:46:04,763 --> 00:46:06,313
But I never stopped loving you.

725
00:46:09,090 --> 00:46:11,295
I thought about you and Brad
every minute of every day.

726
00:46:11,295 --> 00:46:12,895
- Then why didn't you come back?

727
00:46:14,130 --> 00:46:17,743
- Because I felt I didn't
have anything to give you.

728
00:46:19,430 --> 00:46:20,263
Up to now.

729
00:46:27,822 --> 00:46:30,070
- She was supposed to be here hours ago.

730
00:46:30,070 --> 00:46:30,953
I don't know.

731
00:46:32,310 --> 00:46:33,670
Hold it.

732
00:46:33,670 --> 00:46:35,320
Oh no, it's okay, she's here now.

733
00:46:38,130 --> 00:46:39,630
- Where are my birthday cards?

734
00:46:40,639 --> 00:46:41,472
(rock music)

735
00:46:41,472 --> 00:46:42,305
- What?

736
00:46:42,305 --> 00:46:43,750
- And Christmas, every year from Cathy.

737
00:46:43,750 --> 00:46:44,880
10 years' worth of cards,

738
00:46:44,880 --> 00:46:46,530
and I never even knew about them?

739
00:46:47,738 --> 00:46:50,155
(rock music)

740
00:46:52,633 --> 00:46:55,550
(clocking chiming)

741
00:47:07,730 --> 00:47:09,153
- I was going to tell you.

742
00:47:10,090 --> 00:47:10,923
I just.

743
00:47:14,010 --> 00:47:16,903
Andrea, it was your dad.

744
00:47:19,170 --> 00:47:21,320
At first, when you were
little, he thought,

745
00:47:22,320 --> 00:47:23,820
he thought it would hurt and confuse you

746
00:47:23,820 --> 00:47:25,653
getting cards from her, and then,

747
00:47:27,500 --> 00:47:30,000
after he died, I felt you'd
had enough to deal with it.

748
00:47:30,000 --> 00:47:32,382
And I thought maybe when
you were 16, I could--

749
00:47:32,382 --> 00:47:33,882
- You opened them?

750
00:47:34,780 --> 00:47:35,793
You had no right.

751
00:47:37,470 --> 00:47:38,303
- I'm sorry, honey.

752
00:47:38,303 --> 00:47:40,270
I was only doing what I
thought was best for you.

753
00:47:40,270 --> 00:47:43,073
- Stealing the only thing
she ever sent me was best?

754
00:47:48,390 --> 00:47:50,913
- What the hell does she know
about your seventh birthday?

755
00:47:52,710 --> 00:47:53,763
You had the measles.

756
00:47:56,310 --> 00:47:57,700
And I stayed up with you all night

757
00:47:57,700 --> 00:47:59,053
putting on calamine lotion.

758
00:48:03,479 --> 00:48:06,603
For my daughter on her seventh birthday.

759
00:48:08,933 --> 00:48:09,783
- They were mine.

760
00:48:29,060 --> 00:48:30,977
- When are you leaving?

761
00:48:33,410 --> 00:48:34,630
- Friday.

762
00:48:34,630 --> 00:48:35,463
- Good.

763
00:48:37,160 --> 00:48:40,670
If I let you see Andrea
again, you will bring her home

764
00:48:40,670 --> 00:48:42,690
when I tell you to bring her home,

765
00:48:42,690 --> 00:48:44,940
or you will not be
allowed to see her at all.

766
00:48:51,530 --> 00:48:52,930
- Why didn't you adopt them?

767
00:48:56,280 --> 00:48:58,135
- Did she tell you that?

768
00:48:58,135 --> 00:48:59,613
- I checked the records at county.

769
00:49:01,550 --> 00:49:02,873
- God, you've got nerve.

770
00:49:04,470 --> 00:49:05,960
- When Steve and I got married,

771
00:49:05,960 --> 00:49:08,313
you wouldn't let me adopt them, remember?

772
00:49:09,310 --> 00:49:10,660
- You coulda gone to court.

773
00:49:11,750 --> 00:49:14,000
You coulda proved I abandoned them.

774
00:49:14,000 --> 00:49:15,950
- I didn't wanna put them through that.

775
00:49:18,472 --> 00:49:19,305
- Ah.

776
00:49:29,830 --> 00:49:30,663
- [Laura] Why?

777
00:49:33,370 --> 00:49:34,333
- Just curious.

778
00:49:36,260 --> 00:49:37,900
- Well if you're curious
about anything else,

779
00:49:37,900 --> 00:49:39,480
don't ask around at county.

780
00:49:39,480 --> 00:49:40,810
Don't ask her.

781
00:49:40,810 --> 00:49:42,603
Ask me, okay?

782
00:49:43,744 --> 00:49:44,880
- You're so easy to talk to.

783
00:49:44,880 --> 00:49:47,320
- What the hell do you want from me?

784
00:49:47,320 --> 00:49:48,883
You walk in, you disrupt my life, you--

785
00:49:48,883 --> 00:49:51,760
- This is my life you got, okay?

786
00:49:51,760 --> 00:49:54,950
My kids, my house, my life.

787
00:49:54,950 --> 00:49:56,820
- You were the one that walked out.

788
00:49:56,820 --> 00:49:59,560
- And you're the one who
benefited from it, okay?

789
00:49:59,560 --> 00:50:02,550
So maybe you can treat me
with a little courtesy.

790
00:50:02,550 --> 00:50:05,537
- What, you want me to say thank you?

791
00:50:12,040 --> 00:50:14,200
- Can I take Andrea out to dinner tonight?

792
00:50:14,200 --> 00:50:16,140
- No, it's a school night.

793
00:50:16,140 --> 00:50:17,583
- She has to eat.

794
00:50:18,590 --> 00:50:19,423
- I'll feed her.

795
00:50:21,200 --> 00:50:23,933
- Laura, I'm leaving Friday.

796
00:50:30,750 --> 00:50:32,250
- Just have her home by seven.

797
00:50:35,270 --> 00:50:36,103
- Thank you.

798
00:50:42,227 --> 00:50:45,739
(instructor speaking French)

799
00:50:45,739 --> 00:50:49,072
(class speaking French)

800
00:50:52,364 --> 00:50:54,894
(instructor speaking French)

801
00:50:54,894 --> 00:50:58,541
(class speaking French)

802
00:50:58,541 --> 00:51:01,498
(instructor speaking French)

803
00:51:01,498 --> 00:51:03,005
(class speaking French)

804
00:51:03,005 --> 00:51:04,739
- A Christmas wedding at
Anthony's country club.

805
00:51:04,739 --> 00:51:06,050
He's really rich, his dad was a pearl man.

806
00:51:06,050 --> 00:51:07,519
- Wow.

807
00:51:07,519 --> 00:51:10,569
(clearing throat)

808
