I guess every second wife does.

1075
01:07:05,570 --> 01:07:06,970
Thinks about the first wife.

1076
01:07:08,620 --> 01:07:10,920
Wonders what she left
you and why she left it.

1077
01:07:16,050 --> 01:07:17,423
Steve was a good man.

1078
01:07:19,800 --> 01:07:21,050
- I never said he wasn't.

1079
01:07:22,780 --> 01:07:25,330
- You know, it took us
years before we could fight.

1080
01:07:27,230 --> 01:07:28,063
Just,

1081
01:07:29,320 --> 01:07:31,020
fight like married people without him

1082
01:07:31,020 --> 01:07:32,853
making me promise I wouldn't leave.

1083
01:07:41,200 --> 01:07:42,200
How could you do it?

1084
01:07:45,960 --> 01:07:46,793
I mean,

1085
01:07:48,300 --> 01:07:51,360
what gave you permission to just walk out?

1086
01:07:51,360 --> 01:07:52,193
To just.

1087
01:07:53,309 --> 01:07:55,110
- You never felt like you were drowning?

1088
01:07:55,110 --> 01:07:57,860
- Overwhelmed, daily.

1089
01:07:57,860 --> 01:07:59,490
But I could never leave my kids.

1090
01:07:59,490 --> 01:08:01,173
- I didn't know what to do.

1091
01:08:02,030 --> 01:08:04,930
I had no one to go to, I was terrified.

1092
01:08:04,930 --> 01:08:05,890
- They were babies, they were terrified.

1093
01:08:05,890 --> 01:08:07,421
- What did you want me to do?

1094
01:08:07,421 --> 01:08:09,771
Would you rather have me
stay and beat my kids?

1095
01:08:18,077 --> 01:08:20,410
(sniffling)

1096
01:08:24,650 --> 01:08:27,100
I'll never forgive myself
for not being stronger.

1097
01:08:33,280 --> 01:08:34,113
But I wasn't.

1098
01:08:37,320 --> 01:08:38,153
Then.

1099
01:08:43,370 --> 01:08:44,203
- I knew it.

1100
01:08:45,480 --> 01:08:46,702
- They're my kids.

1101
01:08:46,702 --> 01:08:47,560
- No.

1102
01:08:47,560 --> 01:08:49,217
- I've talked to a lawyer,
I could get custody.

1103
01:08:49,217 --> 01:08:50,780
- No, you planned this all along.

1104
01:08:50,780 --> 01:08:53,630
- No, honestly, when I came,
I just wanted to see them.

1105
01:08:53,630 --> 01:08:55,080
But I've already missed so much.

1106
01:08:55,080 --> 01:08:56,270
- And who's fault is that?

1107
01:08:56,270 --> 01:08:59,193
- Mine, and I'm not
gonna screw it up again.

1108
01:09:00,730 --> 01:09:03,249
I'm getting married to a wonderful man.

1109
01:09:03,249 --> 01:09:06,207
They'd have a mother and a father and.

1110
01:09:06,207 --> 01:09:08,957
(dramatic music)

1111
01:09:14,310 --> 01:09:15,250
- You can't go.

1112
01:09:15,250 --> 01:09:16,960
- You little twerp, get outta my room.

1113
01:09:16,960 --> 01:09:18,730
- I won't let you.

1114
01:09:18,730 --> 01:09:21,180
- I have to, she's my
mother, she's your mother.

1115
01:09:21,180 --> 01:09:22,013
- No.

1116
01:09:22,013 --> 01:09:22,846
- She is.

1117
01:09:22,846 --> 01:09:24,890
Whether you like it or
not, she's our mother.

1118
01:09:24,890 --> 01:09:26,830
And I care about her, I wanna know her.

1119
01:09:26,830 --> 01:09:27,803
I wanna know who she is.

1120
01:09:27,803 --> 01:09:29,453
- Then you're not my sister.

1121
01:09:37,535 --> 01:09:39,350
(door knocking)

1122
01:09:39,350 --> 01:09:41,850
(dog barking)

1123
01:09:49,185 --> 01:09:51,685
(dog barking)

1124
01:09:53,820 --> 01:09:54,653
- Laura.

1125
01:09:54,653 --> 01:09:56,890
- Dad, your phone's been off the hook.

1126
01:09:56,890 --> 01:09:58,560
I need that number.

1127
01:09:58,560 --> 01:09:59,393
- [Ed] What number?

1128
01:09:59,393 --> 01:10:00,810
- I've been trying to call you for hours,

1129
01:10:00,810 --> 01:10:02,003
the lawyer's number.

1130
01:10:03,530 --> 01:10:05,440
Cathy wants the kids.

1131
01:10:05,440 --> 01:10:08,940
She's seeing somebody, and
she can get custody, and so,

1132
01:10:08,940 --> 01:10:11,763
if you could please
just get me that number.

1133
01:10:13,980 --> 01:10:15,250
- Oh, honey, I'm so sorry.

1134
01:10:15,250 --> 01:10:16,740
Look, can I get you
some coffee or anything.

1135
01:10:16,740 --> 01:10:18,160
- No, thank you.

1136
01:10:18,160 --> 01:10:20,547
- Well, did she get an injunction or?

1137
01:10:20,547 --> 01:10:23,520
- No, Annie, Annie,
it's complicated, okay?

1138
01:10:23,520 --> 01:10:25,160
- Well does Andrea wanna go with her?

1139
01:10:25,160 --> 01:10:27,330
- Of course she wants to go with her.

1140
01:10:27,330 --> 01:10:28,930
She thinks it's all
about being in a wedding.

1141
01:10:28,930 --> 01:10:31,510
She doesn't realize that
Cathy wants her to stay.

1142
01:10:31,510 --> 01:10:32,350
- She doesn't?

1143
01:10:32,350 --> 01:10:34,100
- Shut up, Annie, just for once.

1144
01:10:34,100 --> 01:10:36,080
- You know, honey, you can
go get a judge that's gonna

1145
01:10:36,080 --> 01:10:38,940
give you a piece of paper
that keeps Cathy outta town.

1146
01:10:38,940 --> 01:10:41,580
But that's not gonna keep
Andrea from thinking about

1147
01:10:41,580 --> 01:10:43,673
or caring about her mother.

1148
01:10:45,430 --> 01:10:47,223
- I am her mother.

1149
01:10:51,600 --> 01:10:56,270
- You know, I was born
to one hell of a bitch.

1150
01:10:56,270 --> 01:10:59,800
Ooh, she was tight-fisted
and she was mean.

1151
01:10:59,800 --> 01:11:02,300
But she clothed and she fed me.

1152
01:11:02,300 --> 01:11:04,990
But the lady next door, my Aunt Jo,

1153
01:11:04,990 --> 01:11:07,070
that was who I went to
when I needed somebody

1154
01:11:07,070 --> 01:11:10,080
to cry on or take care of me.

1155
01:11:10,080 --> 01:11:12,433
I always did right by
the woman who raised me,

1156
01:11:13,280 --> 01:11:16,393
but I did for Aunt Jo because I loved her.

1157
01:11:17,930 --> 01:11:20,943
Everybody chooses their own mother.

1158
01:11:22,468 --> 01:11:25,385
(soft piano music)

1159
01:11:27,354 --> 01:11:29,104
- I can't let her go.

1160
01:11:30,270 --> 01:11:33,160
- Sounds to me like she's halfway gone.

1161
01:11:33,160 --> 01:11:34,810
- But she's too young, she's too.

1162
01:11:36,690 --> 01:11:40,650
- Honey, you can hold
this door open for her,

1163
01:11:40,650 --> 01:11:44,370
or you can bolt it shut and
force her to knock it down.

1164
01:11:44,370 --> 01:11:46,610
But either way, sooner or later,

1165
01:11:46,610 --> 01:11:49,522
she's gonna come through this door.

1166
01:11:49,522 --> 01:11:51,939
(soft music)

1167
01:12:22,590 --> 01:12:23,840
- Have you done anything?

1168
01:12:25,290 --> 01:12:26,123
Legally?

1169
01:12:27,720 --> 01:12:28,633
About custody.

1170
01:12:33,587 --> 01:12:34,420
- No.

1171
01:12:40,300 --> 01:12:41,313
- I could fight you.

1172
01:12:42,554 --> 01:12:43,763
I'd probably win.

1173
01:12:46,320 --> 01:12:48,053
- In a year, Andrea'll be 14.

1174
01:12:49,620 --> 01:12:52,170
Legally, she can decide
who she wants to live with.

1175
01:12:57,852 --> 01:13:00,019
I don't wanna go to court.

1176
01:13:01,440 --> 01:13:03,603
I want us to work this out ourselves.

1177
01:13:04,860 --> 01:13:05,823
Just you and me.

1178
01:13:08,860 --> 01:13:09,693
- And then?

1179
01:13:15,236 --> 01:13:17,153
- I know you love them.

1180
01:13:18,080 --> 01:13:19,330
And I know they love you.

1181
01:13:23,170 --> 01:13:24,870
They're great kids because of you.

1182
01:13:27,410 --> 01:13:29,410
I'm envious of what you've been to them,

1183
01:13:31,019 --> 01:13:33,540
and I'm also thankful.

1184
01:13:33,540 --> 01:13:34,373
- Don't, just.

1185
01:13:39,360 --> 01:13:42,903
I want her to come home after the wedding.

1186
01:13:44,950 --> 01:13:46,070
- What about St. Thomas?

1187
01:13:46,070 --> 01:13:47,893
- She doesn't know how to scuba dive.

1188
01:13:49,630 --> 01:13:50,480
- I'll teach her.

1189
01:13:52,860 --> 01:13:53,910
- Of course you will.

1190
01:13:58,380 --> 01:13:59,373
Okay, but,

1191
01:14:00,520 --> 01:14:02,130
I want her home in time for school.

1192
01:14:02,130 --> 01:14:03,960
No matter what happens,
I want her to finish

1193
01:14:03,960 --> 01:14:06,673
the school year, here.

1194
01:14:08,430 --> 01:14:09,263
- Okay.

1195
01:14:11,140 --> 01:14:11,973
I thought,

1196
01:14:13,420 --> 01:14:16,930
if Brad wanted to, they might both come.

1197
01:14:16,930 --> 01:14:20,180
- Please, let's just get through this.

1198
01:14:28,464 --> 01:14:30,631
(sighing)

1199
01:14:32,475 --> 01:14:33,975
- Mom, Mommy, Mom.

1200
01:14:38,025 --> 01:14:38,858
Mommy.

1201
01:14:40,272 --> 01:14:43,022
(dramatic music)

1202
01:14:52,078 --> 01:14:53,843
Mom, Mommy.

1203
01:14:54,969 --> 01:14:55,802
Mom.

1204
01:14:57,669 --> 01:14:58,502
Mom.

1205
01:14:59,892 --> 01:15:00,860
- I'm here, Andrea.

1206
01:15:00,860 --> 01:15:02,333
Wake up, honey, wake up.

1207
01:15:10,400 --> 01:15:12,650
You know she wants you
to come live with her.

1208
01:15:15,619 --> 01:15:17,769
That's what this wedding
trip is all about.

1209
01:15:19,280 --> 01:15:21,180
Showing you just how nice it would be.

1210
01:15:26,230 --> 01:15:27,897
- I really wanna go.

1211
01:15:34,475 --> 01:15:35,877
- Okay.

1212
01:15:35,877 --> 01:15:38,294
(soft music)

1213
01:15:39,646 --> 01:15:41,979
(sniffling)

1214
01:15:43,325 --> 01:15:44,158
Okay.

1215
01:16:06,130 --> 01:16:08,180
- I thought you might need these.

1216
01:16:08,180 --> 01:16:10,797
It's her prescription
stuff for her cramps.

1217
01:16:10,797 --> 01:16:13,310
And an iron supplement, plus some cream

1218
01:16:13,310 --> 01:16:16,760
for around her toenails, she
has a problem with ingrowns.

1219
01:16:16,760 --> 01:16:18,290
And if she should break out in a rash,

1220
01:16:18,290 --> 01:16:20,610
use this ointment, and
make sure that there's

1221
01:16:20,610 --> 01:16:23,350
no lavender in her soap
or cologne or whatever,

1222
01:16:23,350 --> 01:16:25,890
because she's allergic to lavender.

1223
01:16:25,890 --> 01:16:26,723
- I know.

1224
01:16:31,410 --> 01:16:34,393
Andrea, we better go.

1225
01:16:39,157 --> 01:16:40,290
- I almost forget.

1226
01:16:40,290 --> 01:16:42,553
- No keep it, to remember me.

1227
01:16:43,633 --> 01:16:45,360
- I'll bring you back something okay?

1228
01:16:45,360 --> 01:16:46,193
- Sure.

1229
01:16:49,000 --> 01:16:50,222
- Sweetie.

1230
01:16:50,222 --> 01:16:52,639
(soft music)

1231
01:17:02,940 --> 01:17:04,023
- Have fun, okay?

1232
01:17:10,029 --> 01:17:11,133
- Bye, Mom.

1233
01:17:11,133 --> 01:17:11,966
- Bye.

1234
01:17:13,289 --> 01:17:15,570
You have a safe trip.

1235
01:17:15,570 --> 01:17:17,800
Call me when you get there, okay?

1236
01:17:24,583 --> 01:17:26,773
- Why did you say yes?

1237
01:17:26,773 --> 01:17:28,010
She's the only person in the whole world

1238
01:17:28,010 --> 01:17:29,810
I really care about.

1239
01:17:29,810 --> 01:17:32,400
At least you still have Brad,
but I don't have anybody.

1240
01:17:32,400 --> 01:17:34,823
- Tandy, she's coming back, she's coming

1241
01:17:38,379 --> 01:17:39,212
back.

1242
01:17:41,731 --> 01:17:44,148
(soft music)

1243
01:18:02,868 --> 01:18:06,118
- I can't believe you're actually here.

1244
01:18:07,040 --> 01:18:09,043
- Wow, look at the skyscrapers.

1245
01:18:10,754 --> 01:18:13,260
- You should see the view
from the top of that one.

1246
01:18:13,260 --> 01:18:15,263
I'll take you up there later, if you like.

1247
01:18:16,660 --> 01:18:18,170
- When do I meet Anthony?

1248
01:18:18,170 --> 01:18:19,478
- Lunch.

1249
01:18:19,478 --> 01:18:20,311
- Oh.

1250
01:18:22,007 --> 01:18:23,670
- Do you like this room?

1251
01:18:23,670 --> 01:18:24,980
- I love it.

1252
01:18:24,980 --> 01:18:25,833
- It's yours.

1253
01:18:27,430 --> 01:18:28,643
- This is just amazing.

1254
01:18:29,570 --> 01:18:31,690
- This is just the beginning.

1255
01:18:31,690 --> 01:18:32,790
- Can I use the phone?

1256
01:18:33,700 --> 01:18:34,533
- Sure.

1257
01:18:36,610 --> 01:18:38,953
Then get dressed and I'll
take you to breakfast.

1258
01:18:44,994 --> 01:18:47,494
(busy signal)

1259
01:18:51,960 --> 01:18:53,630
- Tandy, hi, oh my God,

1260
01:18:53,630 --> 01:18:55,540
there's these incredibly high skyscrapers

1261
01:18:55,540 --> 01:18:56,743
right outside my window.

1262
01:18:58,645 --> 01:18:59,478
(dog barking)

1263
01:18:59,478 --> 01:19:01,913
- Hey hey hey now, Duke, you cut that out.

1264
01:19:03,961 --> 01:19:04,961
- You gonna be okay?

1265
01:19:05,870 --> 01:19:07,710
I feel like I'm abandoning you.

1266
01:19:07,710 --> 01:19:10,696
- I'm a grown woman,
Dad, I'm not abandonable.

1267
01:19:10,696 --> 01:19:13,029
(chuckling)

1268
01:19:16,380 --> 01:19:17,943
- Where's that grandson of mine?

1269
01:19:17,943 --> 01:19:20,110
- Oh, he's out back
shoveling snow off the porch.

1270
01:19:20,110 --> 01:19:22,107
- Okay, I'll take him, come on.

1271
01:19:23,470 --> 01:19:25,300
- He likes the yellow one for water.

1272
01:19:25,300 --> 01:19:27,340
Don't ask me why.

1273
01:19:27,340 --> 01:19:30,203
I really appreciate you doing this, a lot.

1274
01:19:31,820 --> 01:19:33,110
- I'm glad Dad has you.

1275
01:19:33,110 --> 01:19:34,910
- Oh, no you aren't.

1276
01:19:34,910 --> 01:19:36,670
- Well, I'm coming around.

1277
01:19:36,670 --> 01:19:40,053
- Oh, good, I'm glad to hear it.

1278
01:19:41,040 --> 01:19:43,054
Now, listen, while
we're gone, can you just

1279
01:19:43,054 --> 01:19:45,780
do something nice for yourself?

1280
01:19:45,780 --> 01:19:47,220
I mean, do something to relax,

1281
01:19:47,220 --> 01:19:48,740
take your mind off everything.

1282
01:19:48,740 --> 01:19:49,660
- Sure.

1283
01:19:49,660 --> 01:19:50,943
- What do you do for fun?

1284
01:19:52,260 --> 01:19:54,051
- Fight with my daughter.

1285
01:19:54,051 --> 01:19:55,051
- Oh, honey.

1286
01:19:57,400 --> 01:19:59,490
(diners chattering)

1287
01:19:59,490 --> 01:20:01,630
- Old people, young people, kids,

1288
01:20:01,630 --> 01:20:04,847
lovers, everyone comes
out, and there's music.

1289
01:20:04,847 --> 01:20:07,580
And the voices ring across the ice.

1290
01:20:07,580 --> 01:20:08,413
You'll see.

1291
01:20:08,413 --> 01:20:10,570
Right after lunch, I'll
get you some skates.

1292
01:20:11,620 --> 01:20:13,510
- Are you gonna come, Anthony?

1293
01:20:13,510 --> 01:20:16,963
- Oh no, as an athlete,
I'm a wonderful jeweler.

1294
01:20:18,580 --> 01:20:19,457
- We'll hold you up.

1295
01:20:19,457 --> 01:20:21,490
- But you will come scuba diving, right,

1296
01:20:21,490 --> 01:20:22,410
on the honeymoon?

1297
01:20:22,410 --> 01:20:23,933
- Scuba diving in Vail?

1298
01:20:25,860 --> 01:20:27,650
- I changed the tickets.

1299
01:20:27,650 --> 01:20:30,103
I thought St. Thomas
would be more romantic

1300
01:20:30,103 --> 01:20:33,380
and fun for all of us.

1301
01:20:33,380 --> 01:20:34,920
- Oh.

1302
01:20:34,920 --> 01:20:36,960
Oh, well, I'm sure you're right.

1303
01:20:36,960 --> 01:20:38,880
- Listen, I don't want
you guys to change if--

1304
01:20:38,880 --> 01:20:40,453
- Not at all, I love the beach.

1305
01:20:43,210 --> 01:20:44,560
- I'll be back in a minute.

1306
01:20:48,220 --> 01:20:49,520
- Never seen her so happy.

1307
01:20:51,310 --> 01:20:53,850
You know, I was very surprised

1308
01:20:53,850 --> 01:20:56,610
when she told me about
you and your brother.

1309
01:20:56,610 --> 01:20:58,790
- Yes, well, she's very
good at surprising people.

1310
01:20:58,790 --> 01:20:59,653
- Yes, she is.

1311
01:21:01,020 --> 01:21:02,780
We wanna have our own family.

1312
01:21:02,780 --> 01:21:04,860
I mean, you're welcome to stay with us,

1313
01:21:04,860 --> 01:21:07,550
and I'm sure as I get to know
you I'll come to love you,

1314
01:21:07,550 --> 01:21:10,790
but, we wanna have our own children.

1315
01:21:10,790 --> 01:21:12,630
You can understand that.

1316
01:21:12,630 --> 01:21:13,463
- Sure.

1317
01:21:15,540 --> 01:21:17,590
- So this business with your brother,

1318
01:21:17,590 --> 01:21:19,240
